You wrote,

> not worry about PGP which may very well be easily broken by the people
> who break codes for a living.

'easily broken' I don't think so...

"Why not use the one time pad?" you asked. The One Time Pad is a PRIVATE key
crypto system as opposed to PGP (and I think RIPEM) which are PUBLIC key
systems. (see the FAQ for full explination).


